title: CMDLine Download via Specific DNS
id: 01d1faae-daa5-48c6-9abd-1af30d7d7862
status: experimental
description: Detects cmdline utilities (wget and curl), set to specific DNS servers.  This is pertinent as Bifrost malware has been observed utilizing a specific DNS Server to download it's payloads.
references:
    -  https://unit42.paloaltonetworks.com/new-linux-variant-bifrost-malware/
author: Tyler Casey @1qazCasey, @scythe_io
date: 2024/03/18
tags:
    - attack.execution
    - attack.1059.004
logsource:
    product: linux
    category: process_creation
detection:
    selection_cmdline:
        CommandLine|contains:
            - '--dns-servers'
    selection_image:
        Image|contains: #modify to include other commandline utilites installed
            - '/bin/curl'
            - '/bin/wget'
    condition: all of selection_*
falsepositives:
    - Administrators utilize these commands for regular work duties. 
level: low
